# Git Commit Workflow

**Never commit changes without explicit user approval.**

Before running any `git commit`:
1. Show the user the proposed commit message and the list of files being committed.
2. Wait for explicit approval ("yes", "go ahead", "commit it", etc.).
3. Only then run `git commit`.

This applies to all commits, including fixes, docs, and refactors.
